						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">samfoo wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">All I'm doing is loading the ROM into memory at 0xc000 and letting it go.</div><br /><br />If you're only loading it into $C000 then you'll be missing out on the mirror at $8000. I assume that is the problem, no writes to the ROM area would affect anything on an NROM-128 cart.<br /><br />You can check if $E9A9 contains $A9, that would prove it more easily.</div>

