					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">It might be easier to describe it as a roundabout form of a pointer / indirect addressing, or masking off certain bits of the address or data lines (over my head here).<br /><br />Using the word &quot;copying&quot; will result in people writing emulators which literally memcpy() a PRG-ROM region instead of implementing the methodology through a pointer.  I remember seeing people do this &quot;back in the day&quot;, actually; was cute to see their emulators running games which do lots of PRG or CHR page swapping.  Let's waste CPU time due to crappy design, yaaeaeaeayyyy...</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

