				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Mirroring is accomplished very simply by using the AND operator:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">u8_t PeekByte( u16_t address )<br />{<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; switch ( address &amp; 0xF000U )<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; {<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; case 0x8000U: return prg&#91; address &amp; 0x3FFFU &#93;; // $8000 &amp; $3FFF = $0000<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; case 0x9000U: return prg&#91; address &amp; 0x3FFFU &#93;; // $9000 &amp; $3FFF = $1000<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; case 0xA000U: return prg&#91; address &amp; 0x3FFFU &#93;; // $A000 &amp; $3FFF = $2000<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; case 0xB000U: return prg&#91; address &amp; 0x3FFFU &#93;; // $B000 &amp; $3FFF = $3000<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; case 0xC000U: return prg&#91; address &amp; 0x3FFFU &#93;; // $C000 &amp; $3FFF = $0000<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; case 0xD000U: return prg&#91; address &amp; 0x3FFFU &#93;; // $D000 &amp; $3FFF = $1000<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; case 0xE000U: return prg&#91; address &amp; 0x3FFFU &#93;; // $E000 &amp; $3FFF = $2000<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; case 0xF000U: return prg&#91; address &amp; 0x3FFFU &#93;; // $F000 &amp; $3FFF = $3000<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; }<br />}</div><br />This is more or less how my emulator does things. Although you could also use biased pointers:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">u8_t* bank_0 = prg - 0x8000U;<br />u8_t* bank_1 = prg - 0xC000U;<br /><br />u8_t PeekByte( u16_t address )<br />{<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; if ( address &amp; 0x8000U ) // A15, ROMSEL<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; {<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; if ( address &amp; 0x4000U ) // A14, ignored on NROM-128, used here to decide which bank pointer to address<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; {<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; return bank_1&#91; address &#93;; // ( ( prg - $C000 ) + $C000 ) = $0000<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; }<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; else<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; {<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; return bank_0&#91; address &#93;; // ( ( prg - $8000 ) + $8000 ) = $0000<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; }<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; }<br />}</div><br />I prefer the switch/case because it's more explicit and easier to read.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

